

# WHEN TO USE MALLOC VS. CALLOC?

In C programming, both malloc and calloc are used to allocate memory dynamically from the heap, but they differ in initialization and how they accept arguments. 

Use calloc when you need an array or structure to be initialized to all zeros immediately.
= CALLOC TO SET TO 0
Use malloc when performance is critical, and you intend to immediately fill or overwrite the memory, making the zeroing process of calloc wasteful. 
= MALLOC IS FASTER; USE IF NO NEED TO SET TO 0

